The sudden noise pulls you out of a deep sleep.
You awake in an unfamiliar bed, and for a second you forget who you are and how you got here.
That's right, your name is azaz.
You're studying abroad in Japan for a semester.
After a brutally long flight, you took a train to this small coastal town.
When you finally arrived at the address provided by the agency, nobody was home.
There was a note by the door, written in English.
(Your host is originally from America, so at least there's no language barrier.)
"azaz - Sorry  I'm not there to greet you! The door is unlocked."
"Your room is at the top of the stairs on the right."
"I'll be back this afternoon. In the meantime, please help yourself to anything you want in the kitchen."
(She sounds nice.)
(The agency said she owns a bakery in town.)
(Maybe she could hire you?)
By the time you got to your room, you were completely exhausted.
You threw yourself onto the bed and passed out with your clothes on.
Now, it's almost evening, and you can hear footsteps and sounds of activity elsewhere in the house.
